title: Introducing: CUPID - A Rom-Com Musical Available Now!
description:
Making up for lost time, Grandpa tells Jason and Dylan about Cupid and his quest for the missing Loomjuice. When Cupid wakes up from a night of partying in Hollywood to find that all of his mother’s powerful love potion is missing, he is stripped of his godly powers and exiled to Earth where he has only 7 days to recover the magical potion. If he fails, his new eternity will consist of constant combat training in his father Ares’ brutal bootcamp. Twists and turns and some unexpected allies await, and the clock is ticking…
Cupid premiered on October 17, 2022, and more episodes are available now wherever you listen to podcasts. QCODE+ subscribers on Apple Podcasts will get early access to all 7 episodes in the series before anyone else and can listen uninterrupted. Learn more at apple.co/qcode. 
Produced by QCODE, Double Garage Films, and Three Amigos. Written and directed by Katy Cavanagh-Jupe. Starring Diego Boneta, Naomie Ackie, Rupert Friend, Dillon Francis and more.
